message:
I've been doing some dev lately and my music collection is pretty stale. I put albums because I like to set it and forget for at least and hour. I'll start this off. 
Tron Legacy - Sound track @ http://listen.grooveshark.com/#/album/Tron+Legacy+Soundtrack/3397401?src=5
Eminem - Recovery @ http://listen.grooveshark.com/#/album/Recovery+explicit+/4610696?src=5

I actually listen to mozart or death cab.  It needs to be something I'm familiar enough with that I won't be in the middle of some deep thought and then get pulled away because I'm hearing something cool I want to listen to.

Beyonce! (http://rd.io/x/QIkgPkD_8Q) Seriously though, I like both the new Tron albums (http://rd.io/x/QIkgPkkk4w and http://rd.io/x/QIkgPkpOpA), Inception (http://rd.io/x/QIkgPkczxQ), and Broken Bells (http://rd.io/x/QIkgPkCPtw). If I need to do some deep thought then it's time for some Chopin. (http://www.rdio.com/#/artist/Frédéric_Chopin/)
Been writing some code to Tron today; gotta admit it's pretty good

Those Tron albums rock my world. And the Inception soundtrack might even be the best part of the movie. And for some reason when the pressure of a deadline looms, there's nothing like blasting any System of a Down album. But maybe that's the drummer in me
Some really good vocal trance over at http://www.tranceislife.com/ About 22 episodes, on average an hour long for each.
